a) Implement Attach Window Activity

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio → Create Blank Process
Step 2: Drag a Sequence

Step 3: Drag Attach Window activity
Step 4: Click Indicate on screen
Step 5: Select the application window (e.g., Notepad)

Step 6: Inside Attach Window, add activities like:

Click
Type Into

Step 7: Configure the activities as required

Step 8: Run the workflow

Result: All actions will be performed inside the selected window

b) Automate using Anchor Base

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio
Step 2: Drag Anchor Base activity

Step 3: In Anchor, drag Find Element
Step 4: Click Indicate on screen → select a stable label/text

Step 5: In Action, drag activity (e.g., Click / Type Into)
Step 6: Indicate the target element (near the anchor)

Step 7: Run the workflow

Result: Automation works even if UI positions change

c) Automate using Element Exists

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio
Step 2: Drag Element Exists activity

Step 3: Click Indicate on screen
Step 4: Select the element to check

Step 5: Create Boolean variable isPresent

Step 6: Drag If activity
Step 7: Set condition:

isPresent = True

Step 8: In Then → add action (e.g., Message Box "Element Found")
Step 9: In Else → add action (e.g., Message Box "Not Found")

Step 10: Run the workflow

d) Automate using Find Children

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio
Step 2: Drag Find Children activity

Step 3: Click Indicate on screen
Step 4: Select parent element (e.g., table/list)

Step 5: Create variable childrenList (IEnumerable<UiElement>)

Step 6: Drag For Each activity
Step 7: Set TypeArgument → UiElement
Step 8: Input → childrenList

Step 9: Inside loop, use activities like:

Get Text
Click

Step 10: Run the workflow

e) Use Get Ancestor Control

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio
Step 2: Drag Get Ancestor activity

Step 3: Click Indicate on screen
Step 4: Select a child element

Step 5: Set Levels Up (e.g., 1 or 2)

Step 6: Store output in variable parentElement

Step 7: Use this element in further activities (Click, Get Text)

Step 8: Run the workflow

f) Use Find Relative Control

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio
Step 2: Drag Find Relative Element activity

Step 3: Set Anchor Element:

Use Indicate on screen → select reference element

Step 4: Set Relative Element:

Indicate the target element

Step 5: Store result in variable

Step 6: Use the element in further actions (Click, Get Text)

Step 7: Run the workflow
